<br>
1. All summoned bags are 100% weight reduction and can hold even the largest items. The difference between the three is not the weight reduction, but rather the number of slots they have. Pockets have 4, holes have 6, glowing backpacks have 8. (I think, I still don't have Gift of Xev)<br>
<br>
2. Magician pets do not need weapons to dual wield at level 39 and beyond. Don't ever give a mage pet a weapon without asking first. The pet will always arm the lowest delay weapons, and the mage may have armed his pet with specific weapons that have a nice proc, or that have resists he wants his pet to have. The mage will become annoyed if you accidentally cause the pet to arm a different weapon. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 52nd Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Drew Davis</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/14/01 9:19:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Small correction</span><hr size=1> <br>
